<subSubSection id="C5DE9CD3FFFE270F659BF90782B19780" pageId="41" pageNumber="342" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="8D7BCF58FFFE270F659BF907857796FF" blockId="41.[151,1436,1685,1748]" pageId="41" pageNumber="342">
<taxonomicName id="4AC4B4DBFFFE270F659BF90780C3969C" authority="Ahl, 1931" authorityName="Ahl" authorityYear="1931" box="[151,475,1685,1712]" class="Amphibia" family="Hyperoliidae" genus="Hyperolius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="41" pageNumber="342" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="spatzi">
<emphasis id="BFB0134AFFFE270F659BF90780469683" box="[151,350,1685,1711]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="342">Hyperolius spatzi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="E955B2A9FFFE270F646BF90780C3969C" author="Ahl" box="[359,475,1685,1712]" firstAuthor="Ahl" pageId="41" pageNumber="342" pagination="1 - 132" refId="ref28575" refString="Ahl, E. (1931) Zur Systematik der afrikanischen Arten der Baumfroschgattung Hyperolius (Amph. Anur.). Mitteilungen aus dem Zoologischen Museum in Berlin, 17, 1 - 132." type="journal article" year="1931">Ahl, 1931</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<typeStatus id="527F71FAFFFE270F64E0F9048344969C" box="[492,604,1686,1712]" pageId="41" pageNumber="342">Lectotype</typeStatus>
<accessionNumber id="929752BBFFFE270F676BF90483EF9683" box="[615,759,1685,1712]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/protein/ZMB32602" pageId="41" pageNumber="342">ZMB 32602</accessionNumber>
, “Bakel-Kidira (oberes Senegalgebiet)” 
<collectingCountry id="F5D38FC8FFFE270F61C5F907843A9683" box="[1225,1314,1685,1711]" name="Senegal" pageId="41" pageNumber="342">Senegal</collectingCountry>
(
<tableCitation id="C046FAE3FFFE270F6038F9078496969C" box="[1332,1422,1685,1712]" captionStart="TABLE 3" captionStartId="43.[151,239,151,175]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="TABLE 3. Codes, localities and co-ordinates for the types and taxa now regarded as junior synonyms of the Hyperolius species, used in figs. 4–10." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/D9BB9FD0FFFC270D659BFF0580AE90FF" pageId="41" pageNumber="342" tableUuid="D9BB9FD0FFFC270D659BFF0580AE90FF">Table 3</tableCitation>
). 
<location id="881B9983FFFE270F65CBF92B800D96FF" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:056D7E4EFFFE270C659BF9DF853A90F9:881B9983FFFE270F65CBF92B800D96FF" box="[199,277,1721,1747]" country="Senegal" municipality="Above" name="Colour" pageId="41" pageNumber="342">Colour</location>
in alcohol: 
<collectingMunicipality id="6D1F5522FFFE270F6494F92B80FB96FF" box="[408,483,1721,1747]" pageId="41" pageNumber="342">Above</collectingMunicipality>
chalk-white or sometimes with fine dark brown stippling.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8D7BCF58FFFE270F659BF89382B19780" blockId="41.[151,1437,1793,2036]" pageId="41" pageNumber="342">
Three sequences were available, all identified as 
<taxonomicName id="4AC4B4DBFFFE270F67BBF89082019737" authorityName="Ahl" authorityYear="1931" box="[695,793,1794,1819]" class="Amphibia" family="Hyperoliidae" genus="Hyperolius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="41" pageNumber="342" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="spatzi">
<emphasis id="BFB0134AFFFE270F67BBF89082019737" box="[695,793,1794,1819]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="342">H. spatzi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The minimum uncorrected 
<emphasis id="BFB0134AFFFE270F615AF89085759737" box="[1110,1133,1794,1819]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="342">p-</emphasis>
distances from other clades were 3.4–6.5% (
<tableCitation id="C046FAE3FFFE270F645FF8B780B6976C" box="[339,430,1829,1856]" captionStart="TABLE 2" captionStartId="20.[151,239,762,788]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="TABLE 2. Uncorrected minimum p-distances as percentages between the clades. GOE—Hyperolius goetzei, NOB—H. noblei, MAR—H. mariae, VIR—H. viridiflavus, GLA— H. glandicolor, MAG—H. marginatus, TUB—H. tuberculosa, BAN—H. bangwae, DIN—H. dintelmanni, MOR—H. marmoratus, NIT—H. nitidulus, SPA—H. spatzi, PAR—H. parallelus." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/D9BB9FD0FFC32732659BFD6880129370" pageId="41" pageNumber="342" tableUuid="D9BB9FD0FFC32732659BFD6880129370">Table 2</tableCitation>
). The sequences all come from 
<collectingCountry id="F5D38FC8FFFE270F662CF8B782619713" box="[800,889,1829,1855]" name="Senegal" pageId="41" pageNumber="342">Senegal</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation id="15FFD3DDFFFE270F6686F8B782EC976C" box="[906,1012,1829,1856]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="40.[151,250,1838,1862]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,237,1814]" captionTargetId="figure-63@40.[151,1435,237,1814]" captionTargetPageId="40" captionText="FIGURE 10. Localities of sequences (black circles), type localities (stars) and location of junior synonyms of Hyperolius noblei (A), H. goetzei (B), H. spatzi (C) and H. dintelmanni (D). Locality codes are explained in Table 3." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6538300" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6538300/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="342">Fig. 10C</figureCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="E955B2A9FFFE270F6106F8B785FD976C" author="Rodel" box="[1034,1253,1829,1856]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Rodel" pageId="41" pageNumber="342" pagination="177 - 188" refId="ref33935" refString="Rodel, M. - O., Sandberger, L., Penner, J., Man, Y. &amp; Hillers, A. (2010) The taxonomic status of Hyperolius spatzi Ahl, 1931 and Hyperolius nitidulus Peters, 1875 (Amphibia: Anura: Hyperoliidae). Bonn zoological Bulletin, 57, 177 - 188." type="journal article" year="2010">
Rödel 
<emphasis id="BFB0134AFFFE270F615AF8B485929713" box="[1110,1162,1829,1855]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="342">et al</emphasis>
. (2010)
</bibRefCitation>
showed that 
<taxonomicName id="4AC4B4DBFFFE270F608DF8B481C0974F" authorityName="Ahl" authorityYear="1931" class="Amphibia" family="Hyperoliidae" genus="Hyperolius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="41" pageNumber="342" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="spatzi">
<emphasis id="BFB0134AFFFE270F608DF8B481C0974F" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="342">H. spatzi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was distinct from 
<taxonomicName id="4AC4B4DBFFFE270F64A5F8D88335974F" authority="Peters, 1875" box="[425,557,1865,1891]" class="Amphibia" family="Hyperoliidae" genus="Hyperolius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="41" pageNumber="342" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nitidulus">
<emphasis id="BFB0134AFFFE270F64A5F8D88335974F" box="[425,557,1865,1891]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="342">H. nitidulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
using genetics, morphology and advertisement calls. The clade is identified as 
<taxonomicName id="4AC4B4DBFFFE270F659BF8FC81E197AB" authorityName="Ahl" authorityYear="1931" box="[151,249,1902,1927]" class="Amphibia" family="Hyperoliidae" genus="Hyperolius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="41" pageNumber="342" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="spatzi">
<emphasis id="BFB0134AFFFE270F659BF8FC81E197AB" box="[151,249,1902,1927]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="342">H. spatzi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as the sequences derive from material collected by 
<bibRefCitation id="E955B2A9FFFE270F663EF8FF851E97A4" author="Rodel" box="[818,1030,1901,1928]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Rodel" pageId="41" pageNumber="342" pagination="177 - 188" refId="ref33935" refString="Rodel, M. - O., Sandberger, L., Penner, J., Man, Y. &amp; Hillers, A. (2010) The taxonomic status of Hyperolius spatzi Ahl, 1931 and Hyperolius nitidulus Peters, 1875 (Amphibia: Anura: Hyperoliidae). Bonn zoological Bulletin, 57, 177 - 188." type="journal article" year="2010">
Rödel 
<emphasis id="BFB0134AFFFE270F6677F8FC82B397AB" box="[891,939,1901,1927]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="342">et al</emphasis>
. (2010)
</bibRefCitation>
. This species is known from 
<collectingCountry id="F5D38FC8FFFE270F6048F8FF848597AB" box="[1348,1437,1901,1927]" name="Gambia" pageId="41" pageNumber="342">Gambia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="F5D38FC8FFFE270F65CBF803803A9787" box="[199,290,1937,1963]" name="Senegal" pageId="41" pageNumber="342">Senegal</collectingCountry>
, and its distribution was discussed by 
<bibRefCitation id="E955B2A9FFFE270F67C2F80382BD9780" author="Rodel" box="[718,933,1937,1964]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Rodel" pageId="41" pageNumber="342" pagination="177 - 188" refId="ref33935" refString="Rodel, M. - O., Sandberger, L., Penner, J., Man, Y. &amp; Hillers, A. (2010) The taxonomic status of Hyperolius spatzi Ahl, 1931 and Hyperolius nitidulus Peters, 1875 (Amphibia: Anura: Hyperoliidae). Bonn zoological Bulletin, 57, 177 - 188." type="journal article" year="2010">
Rödel 
<emphasis id="BFB0134AFFFE270F6614F80082519787" box="[792,841,1937,1963]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="342">et al</emphasis>
. (2010)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C5DE9CD3FFFE270C65CBF827853A90F9" lastPageId="42" lastPageNumber="343" pageId="41" pageNumber="342" type="description">
<paragraph id="8D7BCF58FFFE270F65CBF827856C97DF" blockId="41.[151,1437,1793,2036]" pageId="41" pageNumber="342">
The pattern elements in the descriptions of the 
<typeStatus id="527F71FAFFFE270F67E6F824820297FC" box="[746,794,1974,2000]" pageId="41" pageNumber="342">type</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4AC4B4DBFFFE270F6649F82482B397E3" authorityName="Ahl" authorityYear="1931" box="[837,939,1974,1999]" class="Amphibia" family="Hyperoliidae" genus="Hyperolius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="41" pageNumber="342" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="spatzi">
<emphasis id="BFB0134AFFFE270F6649F82482B397E3" box="[837,939,1974,1999]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="342">H. spatzi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are a uniform back (100%), or fine brown stipple (100%). The percentages are not additive, as the pattern elements may be shared.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8D7BCF58FFFD270C65CBFF05853A90F9" blockId="42.[151,1436,151,213]" pageId="42" pageNumber="343">
The advertisement call (no voucher) is described as ‘a single, pure, metallic and very loud tone’. Mean call length is 
<geoCoordinate id="E8F0A99FFFFD270C65F2FF29805A90F9" box="[254,322,187,213]" degrees="0.08" direction="south" orientation="latitude" pageId="42" pageNumber="343" precision="555" value="-0.08">0.08 s</geoCoordinate>
, at a mean emphasised frequency of 2638 Hz (
<bibRefCitation id="E955B2A9FFFD270C6642FF29850E90F9" author="Rodel" box="[846,1046,187,213]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Rodel" pageId="42" pageNumber="343" pagination="177 - 188" refId="ref33935" refString="Rodel, M. - O., Sandberger, L., Penner, J., Man, Y. &amp; Hillers, A. (2010) The taxonomic status of Hyperolius spatzi Ahl, 1931 and Hyperolius nitidulus Peters, 1875 (Amphibia: Anura: Hyperoliidae). Bonn zoological Bulletin, 57, 177 - 188." type="journal article" year="2010">
Rödel 
<emphasis id="BFB0134AFFFD270C6696FF2982D390F9" box="[922,971,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="343">et al</emphasis>
. 2010
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
